<subSubSection id="C3081DCA6101FFF4FF23FC8F7652C494" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAD4E416101FFF4FF23FC8F7652C494" blockId="19.[192,1440,835,1019]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FF23FC8F7554C434" bold="true" box="[192,356,835,859]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Description</emphasis>
(Figs. 18-19). Length 
<quantity id="4CEAE3A46101FFF4FD8EFC8F76C9C434" box="[621,761,835,859]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.199999999999999" metricValueMax="7.8" metricValueMin="4.6" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="6.199999999999999" valueMax="7.8" valueMin="4.6">4.6-7.8 mm</quantity>
. Dorsal surface bicolored with even setal pattern. 
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FAB4FC8F71A9C434" box="[1367,1433,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Head</emphasis>
: mentum approximately 4x longer than wide, with weak longitudinal trough in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C26101FFF4FB9AFCA87121C414" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="2008" box="[1145,1297,867,891]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Pusiodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mondacai">
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FB9AFCA870BBC414" box="[1145,1163,868,891]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FB7BFCAF7121C414" box="[1176,1297,867,891]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">mondacai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FAFDFCA871A8C414" box="[1310,1432,868,891]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Pronotum</emphasis>
: widest medially, width approximately equal to length. 
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FC92FC487799C4F4" box="[881,937,900,923]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Legs</emphasis>
: protibia with two apical teeth on outer margin, without series of small teeth medially and basally. Claws symmetrical, each side split apically. Protibial spurs absent. Metatibial spurs absent in males, females have 1-2 metatibial spurs (
<quantity id="4CEAE3A46101FFF4FAB3FC0F714EC4B4" box="[1360,1406,963,987]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C26101FFF4FA64FC08757AC494" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Pusiodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FA64FC0871A9C4B4" box="[1415,1433,964,987]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FF23FC2F757AC494" box="[192,330,995,1019]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">flavipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<quantity id="4CEAE3A46101FFF4FE67FC2F7582C494" box="[388,434,995,1019]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C26101FFF4FE5BFC287661C494" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="2008" box="[440,593,995,1019]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Pusiodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mondacai">
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FE5BFC2875FAC494" box="[440,458,996,1019]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FE34FC2F7661C494" box="[471,593,995,1019]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">mondacai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3081DCA6101FFF4FF23FBEF709EC314" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BAD4E416101FFF4FF23FBEF709EC314" blockId="19.[192,1441,1059,1148]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FF23FBEF756DC354" bold="true" box="[192,349,1059,1083]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C26101FFF4FE86FBEF7622C354" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="2008" box="[357,530,1059,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Pusiodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FE86FBEF7622C354" box="[357,530,1059,1083]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Pusiodactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is formed to indicate the similarity of this genus to species in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C26101FFF4FF23FB8F7545C334" box="[192,373,1091,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Macrodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FF23FB8F7545C334" box="[192,373,1091,1115]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Macrodactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C26101FFF4FE6EFB8875E1C334" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1833" box="[397,465,1092,1115]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pisaniidae" genus="Pusio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FE6EFB8875E1C334" box="[397,465,1092,1115]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Pusio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” is Latin for “a small boy” in reference to the very small size of the two species in this genus relative to other melolonthine species. The name is masculine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3081DCA6101FFF4FF23FB6F7572C274" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAD4E416101FFF4FF23FB6F7572C274" blockId="19.[192,1441,1187,1307]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FF23FB6F7505C3D4" bold="true" box="[192,309,1187,1211]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Remark.</emphasis>
Until now, this genus erroneously went under the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C26101FFF4FC38FB6F712FC3D4" authority="Harold. This" authorityName="Harold. This" box="[987,1311,1187,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Pristerophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FC38FB6F70B2C3D4" box="[987,1154,1187,1211]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Pristerophora</emphasis>
Harold. This
</taxonomicName>
was based on a long-standing misidentification of the 
<typeStatus id="54A9F0E36101FFF4FD2DFB087734C3B3" box="[718,772,1220,1244]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C26101FFF4FC67FB0F701FC3B4" box="[900,1071,1219,1243]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Pristerophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FC67FB0F701FC3B4" box="[900,1071,1219,1243]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Pristerophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Now that this nomenclatural problem has been corrected (see under 
<taxonomicName id="4C1235C26101FFF4FD7DFB2F7779C394" box="[670,841,1251,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Pristerophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96692536101FFF4FD7DFB2F7779C394" box="[670,841,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Pristerophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), it is necessary to create a new generic name for this taxon.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
